"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-voices-paris-centre-pompidou-olympics-closed-b2566616.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Notifications\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 13}, {\"ngram\": \"browser preferences\", \"from\": 32, \"to\": 51}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in Swipe for next article Paris's postmodern landmark is to close for refurbishment for five years - almost as long as it took to build - and while its exterior, with its famous 'caterpillar' escalator, will escape mostly untouched,John Grindrodis worried how the iconic gallery might be dramatically 'updated' Removed from bookmarks Franceis having a bit of asummer, is not it?\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 216, \"end\": 221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.231865128601177e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 224, \"end\": 234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmodernism\", \"score\": 0.8904188623518954, \"rank\": 0.12306695452538512, \"text\": \"postmodern\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmodernism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmodernism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the page\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 77}, {\"ngram\": \"another page\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 105}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 117}, {\"ngram\": \"inPlease\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"your browser\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 174}, {\"ngram\": \"Swipe\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 196}, {\"ngram\": \"next article\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 213}, {\"ngram\": \"refurbishment\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 271}, {\"ngram\": \"five years\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 286}, {\"ngram\": \"its exterior\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 348}, {\"ngram\": \"its famous 'caterpillar' escalator\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 389}, {\"ngram\": \"John Grindrodis\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 435}, {\"ngram\": \"the iconic gallery\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 466}, {\"ngram\": \"bookmarks\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 521}, {\"ngram\": \"Franceis\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"asummer\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Massive political turmoil; Macron'ssudden call for elections; theParis Olympicslanding in just over a month.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"elections\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 631}, {\"ngram\": \"theParis Olympicslanding\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 657}, {\"ngram\": \"just over a month\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 678}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is more change coming to the heart of the capital.\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more change\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 704}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 724}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yesterday, architects unveiled plans for thePompidou Centre- plans so big, they will require it to be shut for a colossal five years, and partially closed for seven - as long as it originally took to build.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 948, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"architects\", \"from\": 753, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"thePompidou Centre-\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"a colossal five years\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back in 1971, the team ofRichard Rogers, Su Rogers andRenzo Pianounexpectedly won an international design competition for a vast museum and library.\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"Rogers\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"Su Rogers andRenzo\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"an international design competition\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"a vast museum\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"library\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was chosen at a time when Paris was still reeling from the protests of 1968, and there was a feeling that this new centre needed to feel open and accessible and of the people, not of the establishment.\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1128, \"end\": 1133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.231865128601177e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"the protests\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"a feeling\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"this new centre\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"the establishment\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The architects - then a hippyish bunch of relative youngsters - seemed to represent a new order, their design a demonstration of fresh thinking that was desperately needed.\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1476, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The architects\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"then a hippyish bunch\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"relative youngsters\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"a new order\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1399}, {\"ngram\": \"a demonstration\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1429}, {\"ngram\": \"fresh thinking\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, more than 50 years later, it still retains power to delight and surprise, its futuristic stylings quite at home in an age of new technology and political twists.\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"its futuristic stylings\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1594}, {\"ngram\": \"an age\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"new technology\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1622}, {\"ngram\": \"political twists\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1643}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With its bright colour coding, the Pompidou has a mad inventor's toy box quality that's easy to get excited about.\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1760, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its bright colour coding\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pompidou\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1689}, {\"ngram\": \"a mad inventor's toy box quality\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its most familiar feature, the huge tube escalator on the exterior known asthe caterpillar, is so famous it's now become the centre's logo.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roller_coaster\", \"score\": 0.9999999939227564, \"rank\": 5.8848768420367015e-09, \"text\": \"caterpillar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roller_coaster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roller_coaster\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its most familiar feature\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"the huge tube escalator\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1811}, {\"ngram\": \"the exterior\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1827}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre's logo\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the first large-scale high tech building, a form of modernist architecture that was all about using lightweight materials and making a star feature of its engineering.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first large-scale high tech building\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1948}, {\"ngram\": \"a form\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1956}, {\"ngram\": \"modernist architecture\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1982}, {\"ngram\": \"lightweight materials\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2029}, {\"ngram\": \"a star feature\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"its engineering\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea here was to create as open a box as possible on the inside, with all of the services - cabling, structural supports, stairs and the like - kept to the outside skin.\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2249, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"a box\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"the inside\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2143}, {\"ngram\": \"the services - cabling\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2179}, {\"ngram\": \"structural supports\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"stairs\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"the outside skin\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2248}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a flexible framework that can be endlessly adapted, established as a place where art could help transform society.\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a flexible framework\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2276}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2330}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2340}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And most of all, it's fun, encapsulating a kind of wackyMonty Pythonspirit of the age, modernism at its most outrageous.\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2491, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a kind\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2418}, {\"ngram\": \"wackyMonty Pythonspirit\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2456}, {\"ngram\": \"modernism\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it did cause outrage.\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"outrage\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Critics found it monstrous, industrial and unfinished.\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Critics\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2525}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when it became a sudden hit, attracting five times more visitors than planned, the centre found itself woven in the cultural fabric of the city, just as the designers had hoped.\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sudden hit\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2604}, {\"ngram\": \"five times more visitors\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2641}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2666}, {\"ngram\": \"the cultural fabric\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"the designers\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, some of it has aged.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2787, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These earlyhigh techbuildings are notoriously creaky and leaky.\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2851, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These earlyhigh techbuildings\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also incredible how much clutter accrues over time, and any refurbishment will be a welcome moment to refresh all those chaotic pieces of signage and workarounds.\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 3019, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"how much clutter\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 2907}, {\"ngram\": \"any refurbishment\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 2930}, {\"ngram\": \"a welcome moment\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"all those chaotic pieces\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 2991}, {\"ngram\": \"signage\", \"from\": 2995, \"to\": 3002}, {\"ngram\": \"workarounds\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was something brilliantly handled by architects Feilden Clegg Bradley when they renovated the brutalist South Bank Centre in London, a building of a similar vintage, optimism and oddness.\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3087, \"end\": 3094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Branning\", \"score\": 0.9588710406854529, \"rank\": 0.0406284149042113, \"text\": \"Bradley\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Branning\"}, {\"begin\": 3129, \"end\": 3146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Bank\", \"score\": 0.9999999334086191, \"rank\": 6.659134254517028e-08, \"text\": \"South Bank Centre\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Bank\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Bank\"}, {\"begin\": 3150, \"end\": 3156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997907784964, \"rank\": 2.09177720346585e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 3029, \"to\": 3038}, {\"ngram\": \"architects\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3072}, {\"ngram\": \"a building\", \"from\": 3158, \"to\": 3168}, {\"ngram\": \"a similar vintage\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3189}, {\"ngram\": \"optimism\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3199}, {\"ngram\": \"oddness\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what's planned for the Pompidou goes far beyond that.\", \"from\": 3213, \"to\": 3270, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Pompidou\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3248}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Five years closed is not just a lick of paint and some asbestos removal.\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3344, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just a lick\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3308}, {\"ngram\": \"paint\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3317}, {\"ngram\": \"some asbestos removal\", \"from\": 3322, \"to\": 3343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Architects Moreau Kusunoki and Frida Escobedo are talking a lot about \\\"transparency\\\", bringing in more light by opening up floors, creating a new entrance, dramatically reconfiguring the entire innards of the building.\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3356, \"end\": 3362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanne_Moreau\", \"score\": 0.9986964592747495, \"rank\": 0.0013052420389150859, \"text\": \"Moreau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanne_Moreau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanne_Moreau\"}, {\"begin\": 3363, \"end\": 3371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kusunoki,_Yamaguchi\", \"score\": 0.6593440609799818, \"rank\": 0.37037037037034837, \"text\": \"Kusunoki\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kusunoki,_Yamaguchi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kusunoki,_Yamaguchi\"}, {\"begin\": 3376, \"end\": 3390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frida_Escobedo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Frida Escobedo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q42973\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frida_Escobedo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frida_Escobedo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"transparency\", \"from\": 3416, \"to\": 3428}, {\"ngram\": \"more light\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3453}, {\"ngram\": \"floors\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3474}, {\"ngram\": \"a new entrance\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3499}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire innards\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3546}, {\"ngram\": \"the building\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is talk of introducing \\\"movable partitions\\\", better to reconfigure floors in order to host live shows; a children's zone; and - biggest gulp - an area with two giant circles carved into the floor that can act as a \\\"calm, gathering space\\\".\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"talk\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3577}, {\"ngram\": \"movable partitions\", \"from\": 3594, \"to\": 3612}, {\"ngram\": \"floors\", \"from\": 3637, \"to\": 3643}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3652}, {\"ngram\": \"live shows\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3671}, {\"ngram\": \"a children's zone\", \"from\": 3673, \"to\": 3690}, {\"ngram\": \"- biggest gulp - an area\", \"from\": 3696, \"to\": 3720}, {\"ngram\": \"two giant circles\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3743}, {\"ngram\": \"the floor\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3765}, {\"ngram\": \"space\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3806}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of this is utterly in the spirit of a place designed to be endlessly adaptable, of course - but a lot is riding on it.\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3932, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 3836, \"to\": 3846}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 3850, \"to\": 3857}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 3897, \"to\": 3903}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 3910, \"to\": 3915}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not just the character of a place that generations of Parisians and tourists have been delighted by, but also the generous spirit of the Pompidou - somewhere you can hang out no matter if you have money to spend or not.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4158, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just the character\", \"from\": 3943, \"to\": 3961}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 3965, \"to\": 3972}, {\"ngram\": \"generations\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3989}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 3993, \"to\": 4002}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4015}, {\"ngram\": \"the generous spirit\", \"from\": 4049, \"to\": 4068}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pompidou\", \"from\": 4072, \"to\": 4084}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 4136, \"to\": 4141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For a glimpse of what it was like back in 1977, Roberto Rossellini's documentaryBeaubourg(available on YouTube) captures that moment perfectly.\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4263, \"end\": 4270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1661622418984065e-11, \"text\": \"YouTube\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a glimpse\", \"from\": 4164, \"to\": 4173}, {\"ngram\": \"Roberto Rossellini\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4226}, {\"ngram\": \"that moment\", \"from\": 4281, \"to\": 4292}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a free-form meander, the visitors jostling, whispering and bitching, trying to make sense of the strange new building and its overwhelming contents.\", \"from\": 4304, \"to\": 4457, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a free-form meander\", \"from\": 4309, \"to\": 4328}, {\"ngram\": \"the visitors\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4342}, {\"ngram\": \"whispering\", \"from\": 4353, \"to\": 4363}, {\"ngram\": \"bitching\", \"from\": 4368, \"to\": 4376}, {\"ngram\": \"sense\", \"from\": 4393, \"to\": 4398}, {\"ngram\": \"the strange new building\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4426}, {\"ngram\": \"its overwhelming contents\", \"from\": 4431, \"to\": 4456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When it re-opens in 2030, we can use it to check how much of the spirit of the Pompidou remains.\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 4520, \"to\": 4530}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pompidou\", \"from\": 4534, \"to\": 4546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John Grindrod is author of Iconicon: A Journey Around the Landmark Buildings of Contemporary Britain (Faber, \\u00a310.99) Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4557, \"to\": 4905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4557, \"end\": 4570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Grindrod_(bishop)\", \"score\": 0.9768007113896826, \"rank\": 0.0236686390532643, \"text\": \"John Grindrod\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Grindrod_(bishop)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Grindrod_(bishop)\"}, {\"begin\": 4650, \"end\": 4657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9998806537906418, \"rank\": 0.00011875881014674977, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 4726, \"end\": 4737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.77568607563572e-28, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"author\", \"from\": 4574, \"to\": 4580}, {\"ngram\": \"Iconicon\", \"from\": 4584, \"to\": 4592}, {\"ngram\": \"the Landmark Buildings\", \"from\": 4611, \"to\": 4633}, {\"ngram\": \"(Faber\", \"from\": 4658, \"to\": 4664}, {\"ngram\": \"thought-provoking conversations\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4710}, {\"ngram\": \"their replies\", \"from\": 4753, \"to\": 4766}, {\"ngram\": \"the page\", \"from\": 4782, \"to\": 4790}, {\"ngram\": \"another page\", \"from\": 4806, \"to\": 4818}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 4822, \"to\": 4830}, {\"ngram\": \"inPlease\", \"from\":